<node CREATED="1391661556153" ID="ID_1568215772" LINK="http://infrequently.org/2011/09/why-class-doesnt-mean-what-you-think-it-means/" MODIFIED="1391668414927" TEXT="Classes">
<font BOLD="true" NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12"/>
<node CREATED="1391661747922" ID="ID_894869041" LINK="http://infrequently.org/2011/09/why-class-doesnt-mean-what-you-think-it-means/" MODIFIED="1391662039595" TEXT="Why Class Does not mean what you think">
<richcontent TYPE="NOTE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <font size="13px" face="Verdana, Lucida Grande, sans-serif" color="rgb(51, 51, 51)"><span style="word-spacing: 0px; text-align: start; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Lucida Grande, sans-serif; white-space: normal; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-transform: none; line-height: 20.872499465942383px; text-indent: 0px; float: none; font-style: normal; display: inline !important; font-size: 13px" charset="utf-8">what</span><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span><em style="word-spacing: 0px; text-align: start; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); white-space: normal; font-family: Verdana, Lucida Grande, sans-serif; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-transform: none; line-height: 20.872499465942383px; text-indent: 0px; font-size: 13px">class</em><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span><span style="word-spacing: 0px; text-align: start; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); white-space: normal; font-family: Verdana, Lucida Grande, sans-serif; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-transform: none; line-height: 20.872499465942383px; text-indent: 0px; float: none; font-style: normal; display: inline !important; font-size: 13px">means in ES6 is</span><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span><em style="word-spacing: 0px; text-align: start; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); white-space: normal; font-family: Verdana, Lucida Grande, sans-serif; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-transform: none; line-height: 20.872499465942383px; text-indent: 0px; font-size: 13px">function</em><span style="word-spacing: 0px; text-align: start; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); white-space: normal; font-family: Verdana, Lucida Grande, sans-serif; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-transform: none; line-height: 20.872499465942383px; text-indent: 0px; float: none; font-style: normal; display: inline !important; font-size: 13px">. Or at least one of the things you currently do with</span><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span></font><code style="border-top-style: none; word-spacing: 0px; text-align: start; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); white-space: normal; border-top-width: medium; border-left-style: none; font-weight: normal; border-right-width: medium; border-left-width: medium; font-variant: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-transform: none; line-height: 20.872499465942383px; text-indent: 0px; border-bottom-width: medium; border-bottom-style: none; font-style: normal; border-right-style: none; font-size: 13px"><font size="13px" color="rgb(51, 51, 51)">function</font></code><font size="13px" face="Verdana, Lucida Grande, sans-serif" color="rgb(51, 51, 51)"><span style="word-spacing: 0px; text-align: start; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); white-space: normal; font-family: Verdana, Lucida Grande, sans-serif; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; letter-spacing: normal; text-transform: none; line-height: 20.872499465942383px; text-indent: 0px; float: none; display: inline !important; font-style: normal; font-size: 13px">. </span></font>
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      <font size="15px" face="Open Sans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif" color="rgb(114, 114, 110)"><span style="word-spacing: 0px; text-align: start; color: rgb(114, 114, 110); white-space: normal; font-family: Open Sans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); letter-spacing: normal; text-transform: none; line-height: 25.84000015258789px; text-indent: 0px; float: none; font-style: normal; display: inline !important; font-size: 15px" charset="utf-8">Classes in ES.next are there to provide a declarative surface for the semantics we're used to (e.g functions, prototypes) so that developer intent is expressed instead of the underlying imperative mechanics. </span></font>
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
